Deputy Superintendent of Corps, DSC Okuneye Oyindamola has replaced Chief Superintendent of Corps CSC Oluwole Olusegun as the Command Public Relations Officer for Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps NSCDC Oyo Command. The development according to a press statement signed by Command’s Administration Officer, DCC Igbalawole Sotiyo on behalf of the State Commandant, Commandant Adaralewa Michael stated that a new Civil Defence Public relations officer, DSC Okuneye Oyindamola has assumed duty at the Oyo State Command of Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps. Sotiyo through a copy of the statement made available to INDEPENDENT on Friday noted that DSC Okuneye took over from CSC Oluwole Olusegun, who has served the Corps in that capacity for more than a decade as the Corps Spokesman. “Okuneye who finished from the Tai Solarin University of Education with a degree in Business Administration. Until her recent appointment, Okuneye was the Public relations officer of the newly created female special squad of the Oyo Command. Concluded part of the statement maintained that in case of any information from the Public, the new Public relations officer can be reached of phone numbers 07063848338 and 08058161010 or chooseyqueen@gmail.com.